Description: Shoulder sherd with turn to lip of East Greek pottery closed vessel; interior: plain; exterior: glazed black (fired reddish) save reserved band at turn; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The number 337 is written in ink on the exterior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 337)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 671, no. 298)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.650)
